<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ROCKWELL 9, 10, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - REMOVE -
        OUTPUT YOKE AND OIL SEAL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>OUTPUT YOKE AND OIL SEAL</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Do not work under a vehicle supported only by jacks. Jacks can slip or fall over and cause serious
                    personal injury. Support the vehicle with safety stands. Block the wheels to prevent the vehicle
                    from moving.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put the transmission in NEUTRAL.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put a 2-3/4 inch socket on the nut that fastens the yoke to the output shaft. Remove and
                discard the nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303331">Figure 31)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the yoke from the output shaft. Remove the speedometer tone ring or drive gear from
                the yoke. Replace the yoke if worn or damaged.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a slide hammer and puller, or equivalent, to remove the seal from the retainer. Discard
                the seal
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303332">(Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303331" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303331.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 31. Remove and Discard Nut</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1303332" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303332.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 32. Remove and Discard Seal</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
